---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Sam Onishi"
  description="Fluent in Japanese, English, and Korean—organizational operations, program management, localization, and internal coordination."
>
  <article class="page-content">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>About</h1>
      <p class="lead">Operations-focused partner supporting founders and teams in cross-border and multilingual environments.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Fluent in Japanese, English, and Korean, Sam works across organizational operations,
        program management, localization, and internal coordination—primarily in roles that
        strengthen structure and execution rather than public visibility.
      </p>
      <p>
        Over the course of his career, he has contributed to initiatives spanning Japan, Korea,
        Southeast Asia, and the United States, working within nonprofit, cultural, and early-stage
        venture contexts. His work has included operational setup, documentation design, partnership
        coordination, and multilingual communication support.
      </p>
      <p>
        Sam’s approach centers on building practical foundations that allow founders and teams—particularly
        those navigating cross-border or non-native business environments—to focus on growth, creativity,
        and decision-making. He typically works behind the scenes, functioning as an operations-focused
        partner rather than a public-facing leader.
      </p>

      <h2>Focus Areas</h2>
      <ul class="focus-list">
        <li>Organizational Operations &amp; Internal Coordination</li>
        <li>Program &amp; Venture Operations</li>
        <li>Localization &amp; Multilingual Communication (JA/EN/KO)</li>
        <li>Documentation &amp; Process Support</li>
        <li>Cross-border Coordination (Asia / North America)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="cta-line">
      <a href="/work/">View work &amp; background</a> →
    </p>
  </article>

  <style>
    .page-header {
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }

    .page-header h1 {
      font-family: var(--font-serif);
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 3vw, 2.5rem);
      font-weight: 400;
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--text);
    }

    .page-header .lead {
      margin: 0.5rem 0 0;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      color: var(--muted);
    }

    .prose {
      max-width: 60ch;
    }

    .prose p {
      margin: 0 0 1rem;
    }

    .prose h2 {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--text);
      margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem;
    }

    .focus-list {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .focus-list li {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      margin: 0.4rem 0;
    }

    .focus-list li::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0.6em;
      width: 0.35rem;
      height: 0.35rem;
      border-radius: 50%;
      background: var(--accent);
    }

    .cta-line {
      margin-top: 2.5rem;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .cta-line a {
      font-weight: 500;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
